DEG for recurrence versus non-recurrence in TCGA-HNSC

For reproducing the plots, load the relevant rds files: DEG_res.rds and PlotDEG_box.rds.

Get relevent case id

library(dplyr)
# all cases in TCGA-HNSC
follow_ups=read.delim("metadata/clinical.cohort.2025-07-19/follow_up.tsv")
length(table(follow_ups$cases.submitter_id))
#follow_ups$follow_ups.progression_or_recurrence
#follow_ups$follow_ups.timepoint_category
#follow_ups$follow_ups.disease_response


# 1. Identify recurrence
#    Any row with this id has follow_ups.progression_or_recurrence == "Yes"
type1_ids <- follow_ups %>%
  group_by(cases.submitter_id) %>%
  summarise(
    is_type1 = any(follow_ups.progression_or_recurrence == "Yes"),
    .groups = 'drop' # Drop grouping after summarise
  ) %>%
  filter(is_type1) %>%
  select(cases.submitter_id) %>%
  distinct()

# 2. Identify submitter_ids that *do not* have progression/recurrence
no_progression_ids <- follow_ups %>%
  group_by(cases.submitter_id) %>%
  summarise(
    has_no_progression = all(follow_ups.progression_or_recurrence != "Yes"),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  filter(has_no_progression) %>%
  select(cases.submitter_id)

# 3. Keep only those diagnosed as Tumor Free in the last contact for non-recurrence

type2_ids <- follow_ups %>%
  inner_join(no_progression_ids, by = "cases.submitter_id") %>% # Only consider those with no progression
  group_by(cases.submitter_id) %>%
  summarise(
    is_type2 = any(follow_ups.timepoint_category == "Last Contact" &
                     follow_ups.disease_response == "TF-Tumor Free"),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  filter(is_type2) %>%
  select(cases.submitter_id) %>%
  distinct()

type1_ids$type<-"recurrence"
type2_ids$type<-"non-recurrence"
all_id <-rbind(type1_ids,type2_ids)
#write.csv(all_id,"case_id.csv")

load Demographic Factors, Exposure Factors and expression data

Age, sex, smoker,alcohol,race

load expression data

files <- dir(pattern = "gene_counts.tsv$",recursive = T,full.names = T)

# Initialize an empty data frame to store the gene expression data
gene_expression <- data.frame()

# Loop over each file
for (file in files) {
  # Read the file into a data frame, skipping the first 5 rows (header and N_* rows)
  df <- read.table(file, header = TRUE, skip = 6, sep = "\t", row.names = 1)
  colnames(df) <- c(    'gene_name' ,'gene_type'    ,'unstranded'   ,'stranded_first'   ,'stranded_second'  ,'tpm_unstranded',  'fpkm_unstranded',  'fpkm_uq_unstranded')
  # Extract the 'unstranded' column
  df <- df[, "unstranded", drop = FALSE]
  
  # Rename the column to the file name (without the path )
  colnames(df) <- gsub(".*/", "", basename(file))
  
  # If gene_expression is empty, set it to df; otherwise, merge it with df
  if (ncol(gene_expression) == 0) {
    gene_expression <- df
  } else {
    gene_expression <- merge(gene_expression, df, by = "row.names", all = TRUE)
    rownames(gene_expression) <- gene_expression$Row.names
    gene_expression$Row.names <- NULL
  }
}

# Fill missing values with 0 (since gene expression can't be missing)
gene_expression[is.na(gene_expression)] <- 0

head(gene_expression)

load metadata and merge them to one table

# Make sure the column names in 'metadata' are correctly specified
colnames_to_keep <- c("demographic.age_at_index", "demographic.gender", "demographic.race")

# Extract the sample IDs from the column names of 'gene_expression'
sample_ids <- colnames(gene_expression)

# Read the clinical data file
metadata <- read.delim("metadata/clinical.cohort.2025-07-19/clinical.tsv", header = TRUE, sep = "\t", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Find the matching rows in 'metadata'
matching_rows <- metadata[metadata$cases.submitter_id %in% sample_ids, ]

# Keep only the required columns
demographic_data <- matching_rows[, c("cases.submitter_id", colnames_to_keep)]

# Remove duplicates 
demographic_data <- demographic_data %>% distinct()
print(demographic_data)
demographic_data$demographic.age_at_index <- as.numeric(demographic_data$demographic.age_at_index)
#hist(demographic_data$demographic.age_at_index)
demographic_data$age_group <- cut(demographic_data$demographic.age_at_index, 
                                  breaks = c(0, 40, 60, 80, Inf), 
                                  labels = c("0-40", "40-59", "60-79", "80+"), 
                                  right = FALSE)
# Make sure the column names in 'metadata' are correctly specified
colnames_to_keep <- c("exposures.tobacco_smoking_status", "exposures.alcohol_history")

# Extract the sample IDs from the column names of 'gene_expression'
sample_ids <- colnames(gene_expression)

# Read the clinical data file
metadata <- read.delim("metadata/clinical.cohort.2025-07-19/exposure.tsv", header = TRUE, sep = "\t", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Find the matching rows in 'metadata'
matching_rows <- metadata[metadata$cases.submitter_id %in% sample_ids, ]

# Keep only the required columns
exposures_data <- matching_rows[, c("cases.submitter_id", colnames_to_keep)]

# Remove duplicates 
exposures_data<-exposures_data %>% 
  group_by(cases.submitter_id) %>% 
  summarise(
    exposures.tobacco_smoking_status = ifelse(all(exposures.tobacco_smoking_status == "'--"), "Unknown", names(which.max(table(exposures.tobacco_smoking_status[exposures.tobacco_smoking_status != "'--"])))),
    exposures.alcohol_history = ifelse(all(exposures.alcohol_history == "'--"), "Unknown", names(which.max(table(exposures.alcohol_history[exposures.alcohol_history != "'--"]))))
  )
head(exposures_data)
data.table <- all_id %>%
  left_join(demographic_data, by = "cases.submitter_id") %>%
  left_join(exposures_data, by = "cases.submitter_id")
head(data.table)
write_csv(data.table,"meta_table.csv",col_names = T,quote = "none")

DESeq analysis

test run to see if there are any outliers

library(DESeq2)
library(BiocParallel)
register(MulticoreParam(10))

# 1. Make DESeq2 dataset

gene_expression <-read.csv("gene_expression.csv")
row.names(gene_expression)<-gene_expression[,1]
gene_expression<-gene_expression[,-1]
rownames(data.table) <- data.table$cases.submitter_id
all(colnames(gene_expression)%in% rownames(data.table) )
data.table <- data.table[colnames(gene_expression),]
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
  countData = gene_expression, 
  colData = data.table,
  design = ~ 1 # No group/differential term for PCA, just exploring
)

# 2. Variance-stabilizing transformation (VST)
vsd <- vst(dds, blind = TRUE)

# 3. PCA and plot, try all factors here
plotPCA(vsd, intgroup = c("exposures.alcohol_history"))

remove unknown values and run DESeq2

# no outliers identified
test_coldata <-data.table[,-3]
head(test_coldata)
colnames(test_coldata)
test_coldata <-test_coldata %>%
  filter(!if_any(everything(), ~ . %in% c("not reported", "Unknown")))
test_coldata$merge_condition<-apply(test_coldata[, 2:ncol(test_coldata)], 1, paste, collapse = " ")
table(test_coldata$merge_condition)
test_coldata <- test_coldata %>%
  mutate(across(2:ncol(test_coldata), factor))

rownames(test_coldata)<-test_coldata$cases.submitter_id
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
  countData = gene_expression[,rownames(test_coldata)], # Counts must be integers
  colData = test_coldata,
  design = ~  age_group+demographic.gender+demographic.race+exposures.tobacco_smoking_status+exposures.alcohol_history+type)

dds$type<-factor(dds$type, levels = c("non-recurrence","recurrence"))
dds$age_group<-factor(dds$age_group, levels = c("0-40","40-59","60-79","80+"))
dds$exposures.tobacco_smoking_status<-factor(dds$exposures.tobacco_smoking_status, levels = c("Lifelong Non-Smoker","Current Reformed Smoker for > 15 yrs","Current Reformed Smoker for < or = 15 yrs","Current Smoker"))

dds <- DESeq(dds)
res <- results(dds) # look at the last factor (i.e. type) by default

map Ensembl ids to hgnc

library(biomaRt)

# Remove version numbers from Ensembl IDs
ids <- gsub("\\..*", "", rownames(res))  # Removes e.g., ".17" from "ENSG00000000460.17"

# Connect to Ensembl
mart <- useEnsembl(biomart = "genes", dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl")

# Get mapping
gene_map <- getBM(
  attributes = c("ensembl_gene_id", "hgnc_symbol"),
  filters = "ensembl_gene_id",
  values = ids,
  mart = mart
)
# Merge IDs back into result table
res$ensembl_gene_id <- ids
res_annot <- merge(as.data.frame(res), gene_map, by = "ensembl_gene_id", all.x = TRUE)


# Prepare labels: use gene symbol where available, else Ensembl ID
labels <- ifelse(is.na(res_annot$hgnc_symbol) | res_annot$hgnc_symbol=="",
                 res_annot$ensembl_gene_id, 
                 res_annot$hgnc_symbol)

Volcano plot

We are specifically looking at the four genes of interest. So no need to adjust pvalue here. For instance, the H0 hypothesis for PAEP is: There is no significant change in expression between the recurrence group and non-recurrence group. We only test this hypothesis once.

genes_of_interest <- c("FMO2", "PAEP", "MARCO", "PNPLA3")

# Subset the annotated results for these genes
gene_stats <- res_annot[res_annot$hgnc_symbol %in% genes_of_interest, 
                        c("hgnc_symbol", "log2FoldChange", "pvalue")]

# Print the results
print(gene_stats)

The belowing plot is shown for vst-transformed values, which is not the same as a proper DEseq2 test. It wont account for other factors such as age, gender etc, so the Deseq2 statistics is more reliable. The boxplot here is ok for demonstrating the trends and it would be good to add DEseq2 statistics on top of the figure. Ill do it with illustrator.

library(tidyverse)
# 1. Get vst-transformed counts and sample metadata
vst_mat <- assay(vst(dds))
metadata <- as.data.frame(colData(dds))
metadata$sample <- rownames(metadata)

# 2. Remove version from Ensembl IDs
rownames(vst_mat) <- gsub("\\..*", "", rownames(vst_mat))

# 3. Map Ensembl to gene symbol
# Let's assume gene_map is a data.frame with columns: 'ensembl_gene_id', 'hgnc_symbol'
genes_of_interest <- c("FMO2", "PAEP", "MARCO", "PNPLA3")
ens_ids <- gene_map$ensembl_gene_id[gene_map$hgnc_symbol %in% genes_of_interest]

# 4. Extract expression for those genes and label with gene symbol
expr <- vst_mat[rownames(vst_mat) %in% ens_ids, ]
gene_symbols <- gene_map$hgnc_symbol[match(rownames(expr), gene_map$ensembl_gene_id)]
rownames(expr) <- gene_symbols

# 5. Convert to tidy format for ggplot2
library(tidyverse)
expr_df <- as.data.frame(expr) %>%
  mutate(gene = rownames(expr)) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    -gene,
    names_to = "sample",
    values_to = "expression"
  )
# 6. Add 'type' information
plot_df <- expr_df %>%
  left_join(metadata, by = "sample")
#saveRDS(plot_df,"plotDEG_box.rds")
plot_df<-readRDS("plotDEG_box.rds")

# 7. Make boxplot: genes on x, expression on y, "type" as box color/fill
#pdf("DEG_target_genes.pdf", width = 6, height = 5, pointsize = 12 )
ggplot(plot_df, aes(x = gene, y = expression, fill = type)) +
  geom_boxplot(
    outlier.shape = NA, 
    alpha = 0.7, 
    position = position_dodge(width = 0.8)
  ) +
  geom_jitter(
    alpha = 0.4, 
    position = position_jitterdodge(jitter.width = 0.15, dodge.width = 0.8)
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Gene",
    y = "VST Normalized Expression",
    fill = "Type",
    title = "Expression of Selected Genes by Type"
  ) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "right")
